I mentioned the use case in a comment to BAM-8814, but it really deserves it's own issue.  I'll shamelessly plagiarize myself...

{quote}Our bamboo agent servers run 8 agent instances, which means that each of them have separate copies of the build workspaces. Our builds are quite large, so this is a substantial footprint. If we could configure all the agents on all servers to use a common NAS volume for their workspace ... we'd save over a TB of relatively expensive SAN storage.{quote}

A while back I asked support whether I could symlink each agent's xml-data subdirectory to shared storage and was was told this was not supported.

Currently, Bamboo docker task does not support usage of variables when defining the repository. If a variable is used, the following error is thrown:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed}
Invalid repository name (${bamboo.variable}), only [a-zA-Z0-9_.-] are allowed
{noformat}

{noformat}
BAMBOO is 503 Server Error: Service Unavailable
